3. Why Did the Milkshake Line Change?

Google Trends uses a normalized scale from 0 to 100:
- 100 = peak popularity in the selected time range
- 50 = half of peak popularity
- 0 = insufficient data or very low interest

When a new term is added (e.g., “Breakup”), all values are recalculated relative to the new comparison set, which changes the graph.

